                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17758015" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 23 Aug 2023 13:00:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What do you mean? Is it because the file is &quot;relative&quot; by using DOT SLASH xxx, eg ./myfile.yaml&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also try with only Camel 4.0.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17758027" author="JIRAUSER301007" created="Wed, 23 Aug 2023 13:32:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, exactly, referencing the files using &lt;tt&gt;./&lt;/tt&gt; notation doesn&apos;t seem to work. What would be the command for Camel 4.0.0?&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;jbang -Dcamel.jbang.version=3.21.0 camel@apache/camel:4.0.0 run ./rest-dsl.camel.yaml&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17758036" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 23 Aug 2023 13:40:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okay so its because ./xxx was mistakenly assumed its a hidden file (starts with dot).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17758037" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 23 Aug 2023 13:40:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The same if you do&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;camel run ../beer.yaml&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17758038" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 23 Aug 2023 13:41:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See skipFile in Run command. You are welcome to work on a PR&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17758045" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 23 Aug 2023 13:46:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;camel init has --dir to specify a directory&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;camel init foo.yaml --dir=/myproject&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But yeah it may be better to just specify that in the filename and drop the dir option&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17758484" author="JIRAUSER301007" created="Thu, 24 Aug 2023 09:57:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, I&apos;ll write back when I start working on this, thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=davsclaus&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;davsclaus&quot;&gt;davsclaus&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17766356" author="davsclaus" created="Mon, 18 Sep 2023 12:19:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We are about to cut new set of patch releases so I took a look and implemented this.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
